# Accessibility — Garry Clear Prompt

## WCAG 2.1 AA Compliance

### Project-Specific Requirements
- `ScoreBadge` must include `aria-label` with the score band (e.g. "Average")
- `InfoTooltip` uses `role="tooltip"` and `aria-describedby` to link trigger → content
- `CharCounter` provides `aria-live="polite"` for screen-reader announcements at limits
- All `ExportButtons` have descriptive `aria-label` (e.g. "Download as Markdown")
- `ModeToggle` has `aria-pressed` state

### Semantic HTML
- `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<footer>` for layout landmarks
- Heading hierarchy: `<h1>` → `<h2>` → `<h3>` — never skip levels
- `<button>` for actions, `<a>` for navigation

### ARIA
- `aria-label` on all icon-only buttons (Copy, Download, Trash, etc.)
- `aria-live` regions for dynamic updates (score changes, toast notifications)
- `aria-expanded` for collapsible panels (version history, calibration)

### Keyboard
- All interactive elements keyboard-accessible
- Visible focus indicators (Tailwind `focus-visible:ring-2`)
- Tab order follows visual layout
- Escape closes modals/dropdowns

### Visual
- Minimum contrast: 4.5:1 (normal text), 3:1 (large text)
- Never convey information by colour alone — pair with icons/text
- Support 200% text zoom without content loss

### Testing
- `@testing-library/react` queries prefer accessible roles (`getByRole`, `getByLabelText`)
- Include `aria-*` attribute assertions in component tests
